The paper deals with tracking heavy hitters and quantiles in a distributed streaming model, which involves communication between multiple sites and a coordinator. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. Additionally, the paper involves approximation algorithms and information theory, which could place it in the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The problem of tracking heavy hitters and quantiles is also relevant to databases and data management, which could place the paper in the Databases (cs.DB) category. Finally, the paper involves tracking multiple quantiles simultaneously, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
